Application: Daily Returns of Goldman Sachs Share Prices

rm(list = ls()) 
setwd("/Users/ouyangfu/Dropbox")
GS <- read_csv("gs.csv", col_names = T) %>%
  select(Date, `Adj Close`) %>%
  rename(index = `Adj Close`) %>%
  mutate(lindex = lag(index, n = 1L), ret = (index-lindex)/lindex) %>%
  filter(Date >= "2010-01-01") %>%
  filter(Date <= "2012-12-31")

fig5 <- ggplot(GS, aes(Date)) + 
  geom_line(aes(y = index), size = 0.6, color = "dodgerblue3") +
  labs(title = "Time Series Plot of Goldman Sachs Share Prices, 2010-2012", 
       x = TeX("Time"), y = "Goldman Sachs Share Prices") +        
  theme(axis.title = element_text(family = "serif"),
        plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, family = "serif", face = "bold"))
print(fig5)

garch11.GS <- garch(GS$ret, order = c(1,1), trace = F)
summary(garch11.GS)

ARCH(1)

rm(list = ls()) 

X <- garch.sim(alpha = c(0.6, 0.4), n = 1000)
Xsq <- X^2
sig2 <- 0.6 + 0.4*lag(Xsq)
arch.data <- data.frame(time = c(1:length(X)), Xt = X, Xsqt = Xsq, sig2t = sig2)

fig11 <- ggplot(arch.data, aes(time)) + 
  geom_line(aes(y = Xt), size = 0.4, color = "dodgerblue3") +
  labs(title = TeX("ARCH(1) $X_t$"), 
       x = TeX("$t$"), y = TeX("$X_t$")) +        
  theme(axis.title = element_text(family = "serif"),
        plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, family = "serif", face = "bold"))

fig12 <- ggplot(arch.data, aes(time)) + 
  geom_line(aes(y = sqrt(sig2t)), size = 0.4, color = "dodgerblue3") +
  labs(title = TeX("ARCH(1) $\\sigma_t$"), 
       x = TeX("$t$"), y = TeX("$\\sigma_t$")) +        
  theme(axis.title = element_text(family = "serif"),
        plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, family = "serif", face = "bold"))

fig13 <- ggplot(arch.data, aes(Xt)) +
  geom_histogram(aes(y = ..density..), bins = 50, color="white", 
                 fill="dodgerblue3", 
                 alpha = 0.75, size = 0.1) + 
  stat_function(fun = dnorm, color = "darkred", size = 0.7,
                args = list(mean = mean(arch.data$Xt, 
                                        na.rm = T), 
                            sd = sd(arch.data$Xt, 
                                    na.rm = T))) +
  labs(title = TeX("Empirical Distribution of $X_t$"), 
       x = TeX("$X_t$"), y = "Density") +
  theme(axis.title = element_text(family = "serif"),
        plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, family = "serif"))

y <- quantile(arch.data$Xt, c(0.25, 0.75), na.rm = T) 
x <- qnorm(c(0.25, 0.75))         
slope <- diff(y)/diff(x)             
int   <- y[1] - slope*x[1] 

fig14 <- ggplot(arch.data, aes(sample = Xt)) +
  geom_qq(alpha = 0.5, size = 1, color = "dodgerblue3") +
  geom_abline(intercept=int, slope=slope, color = "darkred", size = 0.7) +
  labs(title = TeX("QQ Plot of $X_t$"), 
       x = "Normal Quantile", y = TeX("Quantile of $X_t$")) +
  theme(axis.title = element_text(family = "serif"),
        plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, family = "serif"))

fig1 <- ggarrange(fig11, fig13, fig12, fig14, ncol = 2, nrow = 2)
print(fig1)

rhox <- acf(arch.data$Xt, plot = F, na.action = na.pass, lag.max = 20)
alpha <- 0.95
conf.lims <- c(-1,1)*qnorm((1 + alpha)/2)/sqrt(rhox$n.used)

fig21 <- rhox$acf %>% 
  as_tibble() %>% mutate(lags = 1:n()) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = lags, y = V1)) + scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(0,41,4)) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = conf.lims, lty = 2, col = "blue") +
  labs(y = "ACF", x = "Lag", title = TeX("ACF of $X_t$")) +
  geom_segment(aes(xend = lags, yend = 0)) + geom_point(size = 1) +
  theme(axis.title = element_text(family = "serif"),
        plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, family = "serif")) +
  ylim(-0.2,0.5)

rhoy <- acf(arch.data $Xsqt, plot = F, na.action = na.pass, lag.max = 20)
alpha <- 0.95
conf.lims <- c(-1,1)*qnorm((1 + alpha)/2)/sqrt(rhoy$n.used)

fig22 <- rhoy$acf %>% 
  as_tibble() %>% mutate(lags = 1:n()) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = lags, y = V1)) + scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(0,41,4)) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = conf.lims, lty = 2, col = "blue") +
  labs(y = "ACF", x = "Lag", title = TeX("ACF of $X_t^2$")) +
  geom_segment(aes(xend = lags, yend = 0)) + geom_point(size = 1) +
  theme(axis.title = element_text(family = "serif"),
        plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, family = "serif")) +
  ylim(-0.2,0.5)

fig2 <- ggarrange(fig21, fig22, ncol = 1, nrow = 2)
print(fig2)

GARCH(1,1)

rm(list = ls()) 

X <- garch.sim(alpha = c(0.6, 0.2), beta = 0.2, n = 1000)
Xsq <- X^2
sig2 <- vector("numeric"); sig2[1] <- NA
for (t in 2:length(X)) {
  sig2[t] <- 0.6/(1-0.2) + 0.2*sum(Xsq[1:(t-1)]*0.2^c((t-2):0))
}
garch.data <- data.frame(time = c(1:length(X)), Xt = X, Xsqt = Xsq, sig2t = sig2)

fig31 <- ggplot(garch.data, aes(time)) + 
  geom_line(aes(y = Xt), size = 0.4, color = "dodgerblue3") +
  labs(title = TeX("GARCH(1,1) $X_t$"), 
       x = TeX("$t$"), y = TeX("$X_t$")) +        
  theme(axis.title = element_text(family = "serif"),
        plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, family = "serif", face = "bold"))

fig32 <- ggplot(garch.data, aes(time)) + 
  geom_line(aes(y = sqrt(sig2t)), size = 0.4, color = "dodgerblue3") +
  labs(title = TeX("GARCH(1,1) $\\sigma_t$"), 
       x = TeX("$t$"), y = TeX("$\\sigma_t$")) +        
  theme(axis.title = element_text(family = "serif"),
        plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, family = "serif", face = "bold"))

fig33 <- ggplot(garch.data, aes(Xt)) +
  geom_histogram(aes(y = ..density..), bins = 50, color="white", 
                 fill="dodgerblue3", 
                 alpha = 0.75, size = 0.1) + 
  stat_function(fun = dnorm, color = "darkred", size = 0.7,
                args = list(mean = mean(garch.data$Xt, 
                                        na.rm = T), 
                            sd = sd(garch.data$Xt, 
                                    na.rm = T))) +
  labs(title = TeX("Empirical Distribution of $X_t$"), 
       x = TeX("$X_t$"), y = "Density") +
  theme(axis.title = element_text(family = "serif"),
        plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, family = "serif"))

y <- quantile(garch.data$Xt, c(0.25, 0.75), na.rm = T) 
x <- qnorm(c(0.25, 0.75))         
slope <- diff(y)/diff(x)             
int   <- y[1] - slope*x[1] 

fig34 <- ggplot(garch.data, aes(sample = Xt)) +
  geom_qq(alpha = 0.5, size = 1, color = "dodgerblue3") +
  geom_abline(intercept=int, slope=slope, color = "darkred", size = 0.7) +
  labs(title = TeX("QQ Plot of $X_t$"), 
       x = "Normal Quantile", y = TeX("Quantile of $X_t$")) +
  theme(axis.title = element_text(family = "serif"),
        plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, family = "serif"))

fig3 <- ggarrange(fig31, fig33, fig32, fig34, ncol = 2, nrow = 2)
print(fig3)

rhox <- acf(garch.data$Xt, plot = F, na.action = na.pass, lag.max = 20)
alpha <- 0.95
conf.lims <- c(-1,1)*qnorm((1 + alpha)/2)/sqrt(rhox$n.used)

fig41 <- rhox$acf %>% 
  as_tibble() %>% mutate(lags = 1:n()) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = lags, y = V1)) + scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(0,41,4)) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = conf.lims, lty = 2, col = "blue") +
  labs(y = "ACF", x = "Lag", title = TeX("ACF of $X_t$")) +
  geom_segment(aes(xend = lags, yend = 0)) + geom_point(size = 1) +
  theme(axis.title = element_text(family = "serif"),
        plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, family = "serif")) +
  ylim(-0.2,0.5)

rhoy <- acf(garch.data $Xsqt, plot = F, na.action = na.pass, lag.max = 20)
alpha <- 0.95
conf.lims <- c(-1,1)*qnorm((1 + alpha)/2)/sqrt(rhoy$n.used)

fig42 <- rhoy$acf %>% 
  as_tibble() %>% mutate(lags = 1:n()) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = lags, y = V1)) + scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(0,41,4)) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = conf.lims, lty = 2, col = "blue") +
  labs(y = "ACF", x = "Lag", title = TeX("ACF of $X_t^2$")) +
  geom_segment(aes(xend = lags, yend = 0)) + geom_point(size = 1) +
  theme(axis.title = element_text(family = "serif"),
        plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, family = "serif")) +
  ylim(-0.2,0.5)

fig4 <- ggarrange(fig41, fig42, ncol = 1, nrow = 2)
